!!!
%html
  %head
    %meta{:charset => "utf-8"}/
    %title jQuery Mobile Docs - Methods
    %link{:href => "../../themes/default", :rel => "stylesheet"}/
    %link{:href => "../_assets/css/jqm-docs.css", :rel => "stylesheet"}/
    %script{:src => "../../js/", :type => "text/javascript"}
  %body
    %div{"data-role" => "page"}
      %div{"data-role" => "header"}
        %h1 Methods
      / /header
      %div{"data-role" => "content"}
        %p jQuery Mobile exposes several methods and properties on the $.mobile object for use in your applications.
        %dl
          %dt
            %code $.mobile.changePage
            (
            %em> method
            )
          %dd Programmatically change from one page to another. This method is used internally for transitions that occur as a result of clicking a link or submitting a form, when those features are enabled.
          %dd
            %dl
              %dt Arguments
              %dd
                %code to
                %ul
                  %li
                    String, url to transition to (
                    %code> "about/us.html"
                    )
                  %li
                    jQuery object (
                    %code> $("#about")
                    )
                  %li Array specifying two page references [from,to] for transitioning from a known page. From is otherwise assumed to be the current page in view (or $.mobile.activePage ).
                  %li
                    Object for sending form data. (
                    %code {to: url, data: serialized form data, type: "get" or "post"}
              %dd
                %code transition
                (
                %em> string
                , examples: "pop", "slide"," "none")
              %dd
                %code back
                (
                %em> boolean
                , default: false). True will cause a reverse-direction transition.
              %dd
                %code changeHash
                (
                %em> boolean
                , default: true). Update the hash to the to page's URL when page change is complete.
          %dd
            Examples:
            %pre
              %code
                %strong //transition to the "about us" page with a slideup transition
                $.mobile.changePage("about/us.html", "slideup");
                %strong //transition to the "search results" page, using data from a form with an ID of "search""
                $.mobile.changePage({
                url: "searchresults.php",
                type: "get",
                data: $("form#search").serialize()
                });
                %strong //transition to the "confirm" page with a "pop" transition without tracking it in history
                $.mobile.changePage("../alerts/confirm.html", "pop", false, false);
          %dt
            %code $.mobile.pageLoading
            (
            %em> method
            )
          %dd Show or hide the page loading message, which is configurable via $.mobile.loadingMessage.
          %dd
            %dl
              %dt Arguments:
              %dd
                %code Done
                (
                %em> boolean
                , defaults to false, meaning loading has started). True will hide the loading message.
          %dd
            Examples:
            %pre
              %code
                %strong //cue the page loader
                $.mobile.pageLoading();
                %strong //hide the page loader
                $.mobile.pageLoading( true );
          %dt
            %code $.mobile.silentScroll
            (
            %em> method
            )
          %dd Scroll to a particular Y position without triggering scroll event listeners.
          %dd
            %dl
              %dt Arguments:
              %dd
                %code yPos
                (
                %em> number
                , defaults to 0). Pass any number to scroll to that Y location.
          %dd
            Examples:
            %pre
              %code
                %strong //scroll to Y 100px
                $.mobile.silentScroll(100);
          %dt
            %code $.mobile.addResolutionBreakpoints
            (
            %em> method
            )
          %dd Add width breakpoints to the min/max width classes that are added to the HTML element.
          %dd
            %dl
              %dt Arguments:
              %dd
                %code values
                (
                %em> number or array
                ). Pass any number or array of numbers to add to the resolution classes. Read more about this feature here:
                = succeed "." do
                  %a{:href => "mediahelpers.html"} Orientation &amp; resolution targeting
          %dd
            Examples:
            %pre
              %code
                %strong //scroll to Y 100px
                $.mobile.silentScroll(100);
          %dt
            %code $.mobile.activePage
            (
            %em> property
            )
          %dd Reference to the page currently in view.
      / /content
    / /page
